Product Requirements Document
Annotation Hiring and Skill Assessment Platform (MVP)

1. Purpose
Build a long-term, scalable hiring and skill assessment platform for annotation roles.
The platform enables candidates to apply for jobs, complete job specific assessments, and build a reusable skill profile, while enabling admins to manage jobs, tests, and hiring decisions.
The MVP prioritizes speed, reliability, and extensibility.

2. Goals
Standardize assessment for annotation roles
Build a reusable candidate pipeline
Enable job specific hiring workflows
Reduce manual hiring effort
Minimize cheating in remote assessments
Support periodic re evaluation

3. Target Users
3.1 Candidates
Annotation job seekers
Full time, part time, and contract based
May apply to multiple jobs and reapply after cooldowns
3.2 Admin Users
Hiring managers
Ops and QA reviewers
Test creators

4. Platform Structure
4.1 Primary Candidate Navigation
After login, candidates see four primary sections:
My Profile
Jobs / projects
Courses
Assessments
This navigation persists across the platform.

5. User Flows
5.1 Candidate Flow
Open signup
Login
Complete profile
CV 
Education
Interests
Ex-Caricular
Are you aware of annotations? And why annotation
Land on the dashboard with four sections
Complete mandatory tests while onboarding
Browse jobs
View job details
Apply to a job / client project
Redirected immediately to the first assessment for that job
Complete assessments in fixed order
Track progress and status
Reapply after cooldown if eligible

5.2 Admin Flow
Admin login
Create tests
Create jobs
Map tests to jobs
Define assessment order and rules per job
Publish jobs
Monitor job-wise candidate pipeline
Review assessment attempts
Approve or reject candidates
Export data

6. Functional Requirements

6.1 Authentication and Profile
Candidate
Open signup
Login and logout
Profile fields:
Email
Phone
Resume upload
Country
Experience
Under Graduate Specialisation
Post Graduate Speacialisation
Admin
Secure admin login
Future support for role based access

6.2 My Profile Section
View and edit profile details
View applied jobs
View assessment history
View cooldown timers

6.3 Jobs Module
Jobs Listing Page
Display all open jobs
Job card shows:
Job title
Annotation type
Employment type
Application status
Job Detail Page
Job description
Required skills
Required assessments
Assessment order
Test rules
Apply and Start Assessment button
Job Rules
Applying to a job automatically starts the assessment flow
Candidates are redirected to the first assessment immediately
If the candidate exits mid flow, progress is saved at assessment level
On re login, candidate continues from the next pending assessment
Candidates can apply to multiple jobs independently

6.4 Assessments Module
Assessments page shows:
Active assessment flows per job
Completed assessment flows
Assessments are grouped by job
Each assessment shows:
Job name
Assessment name
Status:
Not started
In progress
Completed
Flagged
Clicking an assessment resumes the jobâ€™s assessment flow

6.5 Courses Module
Purpose is future upskilling.
MVP Scope
View only
Courses can be job specific or optional
Course completion does not affect hiring in MVP

6.6 Test Flow Rules
Fixed assessment order per job
One assessment accessible at a time
Time limit per assessment
Assessment must be completed in one session
Logging out during assessment ends the attempt

6.7 Test Engine
Supported Test Types
MCQs
Text annotation
Image annotation
Video annotation
Trajectory or sequence based annotation
Scoring
Automated scoring where possible
Manual review fallback
Numeric scores
Skill-wise score mapping

Job Attempt Creation Logic
A job application creates a Job Attempt
A Job Attempt contains:


Candidate ID
Job ID
Ordered list of assessments
Status per assessment


Admin dashboards and reports are driven by Job Attempts, not standalone tests
Skills
English comprehension
Attention to detail
Guideline adherence
Task specific annotation skills

6.8 Anti Cheating Measures
MVP Requirements
Tab switching detection
Copy paste restriction
Randomized questions and task order
Behavior
Flag suspicious attempts
No automatic failures

6.9 Gamification
Engagement only.
Progress bars
Badges for milestones
Levels based on completion
Gamification does not affect hiring decisions.

6.10 Reapplication and Cooldown
Configurable cooldown per job
Cooldown may vary per assessment
Historical attempts retained
New attempts do not overwrite old data

7. Admin Panel

7.1 Test Management
Create and edit tests
Define test type
Set time limits
Map skills
Set scoring logic
AI assisted test creation
Tests are reusable across jobs.

7.2 Job Management
Create job
Define:
Job title
Description
Employment type
Required skills
Cooldown rules
Attach assessments
Define assessment order
Set pass thresholds
Publish or unpublish job

7.3 Job Dashboard
View applied candidates per job
Track assessment progress
View flagged attempts
Review scores and skill breakdown
Approve or reject candidates per job

7.4 Reporting and Exports
Job wise candidate pipeline
Filters by score, skill, and status
CSV export support

8. Non Functional Requirements
Scalable architecture
Secure storage of candidate data
Privacy compliant handling
Performance optimized for media heavy tasks

9. Out of Scope for MVP
Live camera proctoring
ATS integrations
Payments
Candidate feedback or explanations
Notifications and email automation